                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-07-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 13, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. White reports that he is informed by Lord Lansdowne that, at the request of
                    the Russian and Japanese Governments a gunboat has been sent to the region of
                    the Commander Islands for the protection of seals. All British vessels
                    encountered poaching will be seized, and all Japanese vessels similarly engaged
                    will be reported. No action is contemplated against American vessels found so
                    engaged, but hope is expressed that the United States Government will be in
                    sympathy with the above action.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
